    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1919-03-01T07:40:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1919-03-01T07:40:00-05:00" n="871"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d871">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">Paris Peace Conference 184.016/33: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <persName corresp="#p_BAML1" type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Admiral Bristol</hi>
                    </persName>
                    <note n="3" xml:id="d871fn3">Adm. <persName corresp="#p_BAML1">Mark L.
                            Bristol</persName>, commanding U. S. naval forces in Turkey, was
                        appointed High Commissioner of the United States at Constantinople on Aug.
                        12, 1919.</note>
                    <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Commission to Negotiate Peace</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Constantinople</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1919-03-01T14:40:00+02:00">
                            <hi rend="italic">March 1, 1919—2:40 p.m.</hi>
                        </date>
                        <lb/>[Received in Paris March 3, 3:20 a.m.]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>21. “For Captain <persName>Royall Tyler</persName>
                    <note n="4" xml:id="d871fn4">Of the Secretariat of the Commission to Negotiate
                        Peace.</note> [from <persName corresp="#p_RLCEF1">Riggs</persName>].</p>
                <p>Whole party arrived Constantinople. Expect to leave here in a few days. Owing to
                    difficulties of transportation have sub-divided into three parties going direct
                    to Odessa, Ekaterinodar and Tiflis. I am accompanying Odessa party and will
                    visit the other two in turn. <persName corresp="#p_RLCEF1">Lieut. Colonel E. F.
                        Riggs</persName>, Chief of Mission.”</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <persName corresp="#p_BAML1">
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Bristol</hi>
                        </persName>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
